"Abstract This is the full text of a paper delivered by the Hon Justice Michael Kirby AC CMG (Australia) at the October 1991 International Symposium on Information Security held in Tokyo. In it he discusses the initiatives of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) in relation to information security, raising some important questions about the way in which the social implications of technology tend to get submerged by more immediate concerns to exploit technological advances at all costs."
